## Quick Start

### One-function API

```python
from fri import fri_interpolate

result = fri_interpolate(
    grib_file="gmf.gra.2024072412009.grb2",    # CMA-GFS forecast
    dem_file="CMA_Terrain_12P5km.tif",          # DEM terrain
    station_file="Station1",                    # Station list
    model="cma",                                # or "ec"
)

# Access interpolated 2m temperature at all stations
print(result["site"]["2t"])
```

### Class-based API (full control)

```python
from fri import FRIInterpolator
import numpy as np

interp = FRIInterpolator(debug=0)
interp.ltPQ_FRI_Inst = ["2t", "2rh", "10u", "10v", "10ws", "sp"]

# 1. Read stations
stations = interp.dRead_Station_Info("Station1")

# 2. Read GRIB and DEM
grib_data = interp.dRGrib_EC(
    "gmf.gra.2024072412009.grb2",
    ["10u", "10v", "gust", "2t", "tmin", "tmax", "2r", "sp"],
    ["gh", "t", "u", "v", "q", "r"],
)
terrain = interp.dRead_Terrain("CMA_Terrain_12P5km.tif")

# 3. Build geographic grid (CMA example)
grid = interp.dlonlat_info({
    "begin_lon": 70, "end_lon": 140,
    "begin_lat": 0.0625, "end_lat": 60.0625,
    "lon_res": 0.125, "lat_res": 0.125,
})
grid["alt"] = terrain
grid["size"] = grid["ndy2d_x_lon"].size

geography = {
    "lonlat_SL_IG_mdl": grid,
    "lonlat_ML_IG_mdl": None,
    "mask2d_common_12P5km_to_25km": None,
}

# 4. Build target info from stations
target_info = {"site": {
    "lon": np.array([stations[c][1] for c in stations]),
    "lat": np.array([stations[c][2] for c in stations]),
    "alt": np.array([stations[c][3] for c in stations]),
    "size": len(stations),
    "code": list(stations.keys()),
}}

# 5. Run interpolation
result = interp.dCMADMO_3d_Interp_nPQ(grib_data, geography, target_info)
```

### Run the included demo

```bash
# High-level API
python src/fri/demo.py

# Low-level (step-by-step, equivalent to original prototype)
python src/fri/demo.py low

# ECMWF model
python src/fri/demo.py high ec
```

---

## API Reference

### `fri_interpolate(grib_file, dem_file, station_file, model, ...)`

| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |
|-----------|------|---------|-------------|
| `grib_file` | str | — | Path to GRIB2 file (ECMWF or CMA-GFS) |
| `dem_file` | str | — | Path to GeoTIFF DEM file (12.5 km) |
| `station_file` | str | — | Path to station list (text file) |
| `model` | str | `"cma"` | `"ec"` or `"cma"` (accepts aliases) |
| `variables` | list | `['2t','2rh','10u','10v','10ws','sp']` | Variables to interpolate |
| `output_file` | str | None | Optional HDF5 output path |
| `debug` | int | 0 | Verbosity |

Returns: `{"site": {var_name: ndarray, ...}}`

### `FRIInterpolator` class

| Method | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `read_grib(file, surf_vars, pres_vars)` | Decode GRIB2 → numpy arrays |
| `read_terrain(file)` | Load DEM elevation from GeoTIFF |
| `read_stations(file)` | Parse station metadata |
| `interpolate_ec(data, geog, info)` | Full ECMWF interpolation pipeline |
| `interpolate_cma(data, geog, info)` | Full CMA-GFS interpolation pipeline |
| `interpolate_from_files(...)` | Convenience wrapper (same args as `fri_interpolate`) |
| `write_hdf5(path, data)` | Save results to HDF5 |
| `read_hdf5(path)` | Load results from HDF5 |

All original method names (`dRead_Station_Info`, `dRGrib_EC`, `dECDMO_3d_Interp_nPQ`, etc.) are also available for backward compatibility.

---

## Data Format

### Station file

Plain text, first line = station count, then one station per line:

```
2400
54511  北京  116.47  39.80  54.0  北京  北京
58362  上海  121.45  31.23  6.0  上海  上海
...
```

Columns: `code  name  lon  lat  alt(米)  province  city`

### GRIB2

Standard ECMWF or CMA-GFS GRIB2 format, decoded via eccodes. See the demo for exact variable names expected.

### DEM (GeoTIFF)

12.5 km resolution GeoTIFF covering 70°–140°E, 0°–60°N. Elevation in meters. The algorithm automatically handles south-north / west-east orientation.

---

## Model Support

| Feature | ECMWF (`ec`) | CMA-GFS (`cma`) |
|---------|-------------|-----------------|
| Surface variables | `10u,10v,10fg3,2t,mn2t3,mx2t3,2d,sp` | `10u,10v,gust,2t,tmin,tmax,2r,sp` |
| Pressure levels | `gh,t,u,v,q,r` | `gh,t,u,v,q,r` |
| Grid resolution | SL: 0.125° / ML: 0.25° | 0.125° (uniform) |
| Grid range | 70–140°E, 0–60°N | 70–140°E, 0.0625–60.0625°N |
| RH calculation | From dewpoint (2d) | Direct (2r → 2rh) |
| Lapse rate downscaling | 25 km → 12.5 km | Not needed |

